{
  "texts": [
    "The rise of Large Language Models (LLMs) has introduced powerful new paradigms for software and end user development.",
    "With their ability to generate syntactically and often semantically correct code, LLMs such as ChatGPT, Claude, and DeepSeek have permeated professional development environments, spreadsheet systems, and \"no code\" platforms.",
    "Yet despite their fluency, these models remain fundamentally unreliable.",
    "Hallucinations, subtle logic errors, off by one mistakes, and the generation of plausible but incorrect formulas or programming outputs are common even when tasks appear relatively straightforward (Liu et al 2024, Wang et al 2024, Zhang et al, 2025a, Zhang et al 2025b).",
    "This unreliability makes LLMs risky in contexts requiring accuracy, reproducibility, or compliance, such as financial modelling, scientific computation, or safety critical systems."
  ]
}